      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) for hemolysis index QoI must be below 5% on the fine mesh, demonstrating discretization error is adequately controlled.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on the FDA pump geometry. Coarse (2.1M), medium (6.8M), and fine (18.4M) cell meshes evaluated. GCI for normalized index of hemolysis on fine mesh is 3.2%, below the 5% threshold. Richardson extrapolation confirms asymptotic convergence. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid properties) must be documented and matched to simulation boundary conditions within stated uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "Experimental conditions from the FDA benchmark study are fully documented. Five operating points (2.5 L/min at 2500 RPM, 5.0 L/min at 2500 RPM, 2.5 L/min at 3500 RPM, 5.0 L/min at 3500 RPM, 7.0 L/min at 3500 RPM) replicated in simulation. Fluid properties (bovine blood analog, viscosity 0.0035 Pa·s, density 1056 kg/m³) matched. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted relative hemolysis index RH must be below 1.0 for all operating points, and normalized index of hemolysis must agree with experimental measurements within combined simulation and experimental uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Predicted RH < 1.0 satisfied at all 5 operating points relative to predicate device. Normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) predictions fall within ±15% of experimental measurements across all conditions. Worst-case operating point correctly identified as 2.5 L/min at 3500 RPM. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoIs used in validation (NIH, pressure head, velocity field) must directly correspond to the clinical hemolysis risk metric (RH) used in the regulatory decision.",
      "rationale": "Normalized index of hemolysis is the direct precursor to the relative hemolysis index acceptance criterion. Pressure-head and velocity-field QoIs provide mechanistic confidence in shear-stress predictions that drive the hemolysis power-law model. Direct traceability from validation QoI to decision QoI established. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must be performed on the same pump geometry class and operating regime as the COU, with blood-analog fluid properties representative of CPB conditions.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, which is the same device class as the CPB pump under assessment. Operating conditions span the clinical CPB flow range (2–7 L/min). Blood-analog fluid closely approximates in-vivo blood rheology at CPB shear rates. High relevance confirmed. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
