      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence residuals below 1e-5 for all transport equations; mass imbalance below 0.01%.",
      "rationale": "MRL 2 requires only Gradation 1 for numerical solver error. Residual monitoring confirms convergence to 1e-6 for continuity and momentum. Mass imbalance 0.003%. Not assessed as a formal credibility factor per MRL 2 scoping; convergence metrics documented as supporting evidence only."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup reviewed by independent analyst; boundary conditions and material properties verified against source documentation.",
      "rationale": "MRL 2 does not require formal use-error assessment beyond Gradation 1. An independent internal review of simulation setup was conducted informally. Boundary conditions and material properties were cross-checked against the experimental protocol. Not formally assessed per MRL 2 scoping decision."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The continuum fluid mechanics and power-law hemolysis model forms are appropriate for the flow regime and shear-rate range encountered in the CPB pump.",
      "rationale": "MRL 2 Gradation 1 requirement for model form does not mandate formal sensitivity analysis of model-form assumptions. The k-omega SST turbulence model and Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power law are standard choices for blood pump CFD, supported by published literature. Not formally assessed per MRL 2 scoping."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
